article.headline: Bradley 79, SMS 72
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Phillip Gilbert scored 31 points as Bradley beat Southwest Missouri State 79-72 Monday night. Bradley (15-15, 7-11 Missouri Valley) took a 33-27 lead at the half and stayed in control behind J.J. Tauai with 19 points and Marcellus Sommerville with 16 and 9 rebounds. The difference in the game was Bradley converting 35-of-40 from the foul line while Southwest Missouri State (17-13, 9-9) was 21-of-29. Gilbert led the Braves going 21-of-22 from the line. While Bradley converted 17-of-42 from the field, they were 10-of-20 on 3-pointers. Southwest Missouri State was led by Merrill Andrews with 18 points and Monwell Randle added 14.
